STEP 1 — Create hrms_store.py service layer
==============================================================================
Create file: app/services/hrms_store.py

This mirrors timesheet_store.py for HRMS. All functions take a `db: Session` parameter and run SQL queries.

Functions to implement:

  list_leave_types(db) -> list[dict]
    Returns all leave types: [{leave_type_id, name, max_days, created_by, created_date}]
    Date columns converted to YYYY-MM-DD strings.

  create_leave_type(db, name, max_days, created_by) -> dict
    Inserts into hr_leave_types_demo. Sets CreatedDate to today.
    Returns the created row as dict.

  list_leave_requests(db, resource_id=None, is_approved=None) -> list[dict]
    Joins hr_leave_requests_demo with hr_leave_types_demo to get leave type names.
    Filters by resource_id if provided.
    Filters by is_approved if provided: "PENDING", "APPROVED", "REJECTED".
    Returns: [{request_id, resource_id, leave_type_id, leave_type_name, from_date, to_date, num_days, reason, status, approved_by, approver_remarks, created_date}]
    Status mapping: NULL→"PENDING", 1→"APPROVED", 0→"REJECTED"
    Dates as YYYY-MM-DD strings.

  create_leave_request(db, resource_id, leave_type_id, from_date, to_date, reason) -> dict
    Inserts a new pending request (IsApproved=NULL).
    NumDays computed as (to_date - from_date) + 1 (inclusive).
    CreatedDate = today.
    Returns the created row.

  approve_leave_request(db, request_id, approver_id, decision, remarks="") -> dict
    Updates row: IsApproved = 1 (APPROVED) or 0 (REJECTED), ApprovedBy, ApprovedDate=today, ApproverRemarks.
    decision parameter: "APPROVED" or "REJECTED" (uppercase string).
    Returns {success, request_id, new_status, approver}.
    If request not found or already decided, return {"error": "..."} dict.

  compute_leave_balance(db, resource_id) -> list[dict]
    For each leave type, compute remaining days = MaxDays - SUM(NumDays of APPROVED requests for this resource for this leave type).
    Returns: [{leave_type_id, leave_type_name, max_days, used_days, remaining_days}]
    Only count IsApproved=1 (approved). Ignore pending and rejected.

  list_payslips(db, resource_id=None, pay_month=None) -> list[dict]
    Returns payslips. Filter by resource_id if provided. Filter by pay_month if provided.
    Returns: [{payslip_id, resource_id, pay_month, basic, allowances, deductions, net_pay, created_by, created_date}]

  create_payslip(db, resource_id, pay_month, basic, allowances, deductions, created_by) -> dict
    Inserts new payslip. NetPay = basic + allowances - deductions. CreatedDate = today.
    Returns the created row.

